                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1112</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-19T00:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1917, midnight</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 18, 7 p.m. Publication of statement has produced marked impression.
                    Cuban Secretary of State and the President have made feeling response. From my
                    viewpoint and understanding of conditions here the message leaves nothing to be
                    desired in form, spirit or principle.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
